schools.name: Bonita Springs Middle Center For The Arts

data.description: "An Exceptional Opportunity in the Heart of Bonita Springs Historic District!  This charming single-family home is situated in a T4 / Residential & Commercial zone, with the newly modernized Bonita Springs Library as its neighbor, providing a vibrant and walkable city environment. The T4 Zone allows for the potential addition of another residential unit or a side yard house on this lot .  This property offers the perfect fusion of residence and business. It is tailored for short-term tourist rentals with a proven track record of rental income. Nestled amidst natural parks, a kayaking river, a zoo, an art festival area, and a secure family-friendly environment, all these attractions are within easy walking distance.   This property has garnered a remarkable 5-star rating from previous guests who have enjoyed their stay here.  Don't miss this opportunity to own a piece of the picturesque and beloved Historic District of Bonita Springs. You can choose to live here, realize your business dream, or even embrace the best of both worlds!"  Additionally, the seller is requesting a 45-day leaseback after the closing.
